Cook, please see my last post on #1, then read this.<br><br>
My concerns is that &quot;we&quot; possibly are stopping others from voicing their concerns, their feelings, or their pain, while we play warfare between us.  Your post above is a masterpiece of insult and attack, but what good does this do? I may lower your blood pressure, but it may chase away someone who really needs to post, be they veteran or protestor.  VietSon was rudely treated, as was Richard. So Richard ran to Canada, that was part of the entire reality at the time. I didn't. I would like to know more about what he and his life are, but you chased him off.  That is unfortunate.  By the way, I guess being a homosexual is bad to you (sorry, I am not one), but you baffled me by saying that I was one and that I also had sons in the same line asking me what I did in the war.  <br><br>
Calm down man. You may be the most closed and narrow minded bigot I have ever met, but I still don't want you to blow a gasket.  <br><br>
This is not your thread, nor site. Nor is it mine. It belongs technically to POV and Marc Weiss (another commie jew bastard by the way), and we are all blessed with this place.  When the site was in danger of folding, it was us &quot;old timers&quot; (who now mostly won't get involved-and who can blame them-in this pig pen) who rallied the troops and did what we could to urge POV to continue it on.  They did. They won and in doing so we all won.  Even you, although it was before you even knew this site was here.<br><br>
What was the purpose of you last post?  I am flattered I guess that you spent all those words and time to attack me on every level you could think of. But what does that have to do with the War in Viet Nam and how it impacted each and everyone of us?  <br><br>
Sorry Cook. I am not a commie, nor a coward. I am not a homosexual, nor a bisexual. I (hope you are sitting down) am a card carrying Republican with a bit of Libertarian mixed in.  I have more ex-police officer friends then I can count. Also have intellectuals, professionals, gays, straights, minorities, majorities, women, men, and even, even, veterans of the war in Viet Nam.  And I have a list of friends who came home in body bags too.  So what.  I know you do too.<br><br>
I got over you a long time ago, Cook, but what is it that you can't let go of with me?  Your persistent insults are so petty that I have to laugh, like the reference to a night light. Really Cook, you used to do better than that.<br><br>
I think you have singled me out for your &quot;love-hate&quot; affair because I represent the single fact that you can't come to terms with.  As big and brave, and macho you say you were as a soldier, and later as a Peace Officer, the simple truth is the war in Viet Nam was wrong. PERIOD. Wrong, a mistake, a tragic mistake that killed too many people on both sides, for nothing but the gain of the politicians.  That should tell you a tremendous secret and truth: War sucks. <br><br>
Rather than lunch with you some day, (I don't do C rations or span), but I have qualified on almost every gun range in Southern California, I rather see which of us is the better shot.  We can't have a war of wits or words, cause that has already been decided.  We can have a contest of marksmenship, perhaps, and when &quot;the little commie&quot; shoots you off the range, you can then apologize for all your demeaning and petty bullshit behavior. <br><br>
Behind your back, Cook, b/c I get alot of e mail, and brother, the majority do not like you. They think you are a big and foul mouthed bully. I tell them to post it. They don't want to. Can't say I blame them.  You do get to be too much some times.  5 daughters did you say? God help your son-in-laws.<br><br>
Anyway Cook, got to go now, got my marxist-leninist-mao study group meeting tonight, where we will be plotting the homosexual takeover of all police departments by lesbians and cowards.  Jesus C, Cook, get a grip, and a sense of humor.  The war is over, haven't you heard?<br><br>

